16/12/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Outgoing Prime Minister Ivica Racan meets his likely successor Ivo Sanader on Tuesday (16 December).
Sanader was nominated to form the country's new cabinet as leader of the Croatian Democratic Union.
This is the first meeting of the two since the 23 November parliamentary elections.
In other news, Slovene Prime Minister Anton Rop told reporters in Ljubljana that his government looks forward to negotiations with the new Croatian government.
He said the election created opportunities to resolve open issues.
(Vjesnik - 16/12/03;
HINA, STA - 15/12/03)
